In case every csv file is going to have first row as header, you can use following syntax on athena to create the required table in Glue Catalog :


    CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS {{tablename}} ({{headers}}) 
    ROW FORMAT SERDE &#39;org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.OpenCSVSerde&#39; 
    WITH SERDEPROPERTIES ( &#39;escapeChar&#39;=&#39;/&#39;, &#39;quoteChar&#39;=&#39;\\&quot;&#39;, &#39;separatorChar&#39;=&#39;,&#39;) 
    STORED AS INPUTFORMAT &#39;org.apache.hadoop.mapred.TextInputFormat&#39; 
    OUTPUTFORMAT &#39;org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.HiveIgnoreKeyTextOutputFormat&#39; 
    LOCATION &#39;{{location}}&#39; TBLPROPERTIES (&#39;skip.header.line.count&#39;=&#39;1&#39;)&quot;

Replace the place holders {{tablename}}, {{headers}} and {{location}} with respective values.

Even better solution would be to stop generating the header rows in the CSV itself, and then you can impose your own schema/headers on top of it with CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE command in athena  or through Glue Crawler.

